ce:section.ce:para:
Bubble Sets aim to satisfy the following: (a)
for each set, all set members are to be enclosed by the closed curve representing that set,(b)
for each set, non-set members, if possible, are to be excluded from the closed curve representing that set,(c)
where non-members appear within curve boundaries, visual and interactive hints can be given to clarify membership, and(d)
to provide rendering to allow for interactive adjustment.
